column2: West wind 5-10 mph- partly sunny- 62 degrees.  40+ buffleheads still on lake.

Bottom visible from point east to east shore this deepest spot (map wrong) 9.5' south of point can see bottom.  Floating algae collecting on calm shore line.  Sunny 68 degrees- variable light wind.  Took readings both south and east from p
Cloudy- light wind- 64 degrees- floating algae now covering close to 1/4 of the lake.
Cloudy- wind NW 10 mph- 60 degrees.  Floating algae along south shore.  Green slimy algae on weeds by the islands.  Floating algae also being held by weeds on part of east side.
Sunny- SE to E variable wind.  Slimy green algae turning brown on weeds.  Floating algae covered 1/2 lake before winds came.  Four pair geese have 31 gosling on lake this year.
Sunny- south wind 5-10- 89 degrees.  75% floating algae on lake until wind came up-then about 40% coverage.  Weeds worse than ever this year.
Overcast- light SW winds- 78 degrees.  Duckwort mixed with floating algae on 10% of lake.
Partly cloudy- variable light wind- 72 degrees- no floating algae due to break-up from rain + strong winds yesterday.  Kids swimming by boat landing.
Sunny- wind calm to light- 86 degrees- floating algae along most of the shore 5 to 20'.
Partly sunny- light south wind- 68 degrees- floating algae broken up and being pushed to north shore of lake- effecting about 1/3 of the lake.
Cloudy- south wind 10-15 mph- 74 degrees- very little floating algae.  Long time residents say water clarity worst they have seen on lake.  Bald eagle fishing + caught bass today.
82 degrees- partly cloudy- light south wind.
82 degrees- partly sunny- south wind 10 mph- 3" of rain this week.
Partly sunny- 76 degrees- light south wind.  Disc shows clear/blue first 1.75' then begins to show green.
Sunny- 74 degrees- NW wind 10-15 mph- floating algae covered lake before wind-now in big chunks below surface.  Eagle still here.
60 degrees- sunny- NW light wind- small clumps of floating algae.  2 mature eagles on lake today.
58 degrees- partly sunny- northwest-southwest variable wind-floating algae on most of lake-boat landing closed in by algae-no boats on lake except me.
52 degrees- mostly cloudy- calm to light north wind-some floating algae-pushed up along south shore.
14:00 partly cloudy- light south wind.  Bottom can be seen without secchi disc.  Floating algae on north side of lake.
Sunny- light south wind- 58 degrees.  Over 100 Canada geese on lake today.
Partly sunny- west wind- 40 degrees- took boat out- two eagles fishing this week.  Lake produced 31 geese- 14 mallard and 4 wood duck.  Snapping turtles took many small mallards this year.
Sunny- 52 degrees- NW wind 10-20 mph. 29 cormorants killing trout- 2 osprey- 1 bald eagle on lake also.
50 degrees- wind variable 0-15 mph- partly sunny.
62 degrees- wind east 5-10- reading taken at dam.
Partly sunny- east wind.  56 degrees- floating algae on north end of lake and along part of eastern shore.
75 degrees- W wind @ 10 mph.  Heavy slim algae weed growth all over lake.  Floating algae from island north- west + south shores covered with floating algae.
86 degrees- sunny- light variable wind floating algae 80% weeds high almost to the surface even in deep water.
68 degrees- partly cloudy- SW wind 10-15 mph- very weedy- few fishermen because of weeds.  Floating algae east shore of and from island north.
88 degrees- SE wind light and weed choking off island and very thick west of point.
Public perception due to weed level.  Weeds choke out outboard motors. weeds hide disc in deeper water- 80 degrees- sunny- light variable wind- floating algae on east half of the lake.
82 degrees- sunny- no wind- floating algae covering most of lake.
